On Thu, 27 Feb 2003, Chuck Hinson wrote:
&gt; So if I have a really large user population and I want 250000 of them to
&gt; have access to a particular document document or resource, you want me
&gt; to create 250000 different URLs?

Depends on your application.  In many application
domains, it is completely reasonable to generate a
different URL in each announcment email.

Alternatively:

&gt; &gt;You POST credentials to a login resource and
&gt; &gt;receive a redirect to the restricted URL.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; But how do I relate that login resource to the resources that are protected?

You have a login resource per protected resource
or resources.

One REST pattern is that applications should
expose a single root URL from which you navigate
to the others.  So the redirect should probably be
to this root.

-Alex-

